B.C. police officer, who was shot and killed in June, remembered at 10-year-old memorial
Bobby Lee Lee, who was shot and killed during a police pursuit on a Vancouver Island highway, is being remembered 10 years after his death.

A new police chief was also sworn in at a ceremony in Surrey on Tuesday.

Bobby Lee Lee was shot and killed June 6, 2008. The 55-year-old Surrey native was a member of the Combined Law Enforcement Emergency Services Unit and Surrey police. (Global News)
